rounds.event: The United Kingdom ends its protectorate over Egypt through a Unilateral Declaration of Independence.
Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms (ATF) agents raid the Branch Davidian church in Waco, Texas with a warrant to arrest the group's leader David Koresh, starting a 51-day standoff.
deaths: Ruby Keeler, Canadian-American actress and dancer

rounds.event: During the religious violence in Gujarat, 97 people are killed in the Naroda Patiya massacre and 69 in the Gulbarg Society massacre.
deaths: Mary Stuart, American actress and singer
Helmut Zacharias, German violinist and composer

rounds.event: Discoverer 1, an American spy satellite that is the first object intended to achieve a polar orbit, is launched but fails to achieve orbit.
Two trains collide south of the Vale of Tempe in Greece, leading to the deaths of at least 57 people and leaving 58 missing and 85 injured.
